1
00:00:01,590 --> 00:00:04,080
- Ouji?
- Let's break up.

2
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,950
Sorry.

3
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:17,080
I'm just... sorry.

4
00:00:19,930 --> 00:00:24,430
Haru, I think you're cute, and I cherish you.

5
00:00:28,130 --> 00:00:31,360
But my body refuses to respond.

6
00:00:33,930 --> 00:00:40,000
I haven't been able to get it up,
with anyone.

7
00:00:45,910 --> 00:00:48,030
Get it... up?

8
00:00:51,610 --> 00:00:56,380
Well... I know there are remedies.

9
00:00:56,380 --> 00:00:59,100
I've heard about them before.

10
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,390
I can help look into it.

11
00:01:02,150 --> 00:01:05,010
Mind if I take a smoke?

12
00:01:20,910 --> 00:01:23,450
It's freezing out here.

13
00:01:41,830 --> 00:01:43,500
Thanks.

14
00:01:50,450 --> 00:01:56,050
It was boiling during our ceremony.
Has it been half a year already?

15
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:01,510
It's been about three months.

16
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:04,700
Oh.

17
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:10,510
Guess I'm finally paying the price, huh?

18
00:02:10,510 --> 00:02:12,240
What?

19
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:18,100
I've never actually enjoyed sex before.

20
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:19,260
What?

21
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:21,200
Ouch, my ear.

22
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,690
Sorry, it's just...

23
00:02:23,690 --> 00:02:28,350
I became insanely popular
when I debuted with the band.

24
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:31,160
Sure, at first I let myself bask in it.

25
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,050
But over time...

26
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:37,280
Girls would imagine their own versions of me,

27
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:40,700
and come at me aggressively
in the name of "love".

28
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:43,510
Eventually, I got fed up with it all.

29
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:49,170
I couldn't stand these girls
having their way with me,

30
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:51,960
so I decided to go on the offensive
before they could.

31
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,040
To eat, before I was eaten, if you will.

32
00:02:57,470 --> 00:03:03,550
Repeat that cycle,
and I ultimately ran myself dry.

33
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:07,000
Both my body and heart, emptied out.

34
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:14,680
And then the kidney stone? Poor me.

35
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:19,620
You really do reap what you sow.

36
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:22,520
That's not...

37
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:28,760
You came to care for me after that debacle.

38
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:32,060
It was a huge help, sure.

39
00:03:32,060 --> 00:03:35,420
But I thought you'd ultimately ask
for the same thing,

40
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:40,070
only to be disappointed
I had nothing to offer.

41
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,320
Except, you were different.

42
00:03:45,650 --> 00:03:49,530
You made no moves.
You completely ignored my room.

43
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:53,280
That's because your room was...

44
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:56,100
It seriously put me at ease.

45
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,600
You saved me.

46
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,560
Sorry.

47
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:52,110
Let's break up after all.

48
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:57,640
If you stay, you won't ever get to have sex.

49
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,050
No.

50
00:05:03,540 --> 00:05:05,440
I don't want to break up.

51
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:08,600
I saved you?

52
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,920
Well, you saved me.

53
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,090
Of course I want to stay with you.

54
00:05:12,090 --> 00:05:15,400
But don't you want to have sex?

55
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:20,670
Sorry.

56
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:24,530
I don't mean that in a bad way, really.

57
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:29,820
In the end, it's all my fault.

58
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:35,620
I won't touch you again, I promise.

59
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:45,640
I'm sorry our marriage turned out like this.

60
00:06:53,410 --> 00:06:57,580
[Episode 6]

61
00:07:03,170 --> 00:07:06,640
<i>Sorry. Let's break up after all.</i>

62
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:10,370
<i>If you stay, you won't ever get to have sex.</i>

63
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,860
[Open Relationships]

64
00:07:18,860 --> 00:07:22,480
[Couples who consensually have sex
with other partners]

65
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,900
Unbelievable.

66
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:27,410
Something the matter?

67
00:07:29,150 --> 00:07:30,650
No.

68
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:41,310
<i>I'm sorry our marriage turned out like this.</i>

69
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:48,290
What the hell, man?

70
00:07:48,290 --> 00:07:53,090
Got into an argument with Haru?

71
00:07:53,090 --> 00:07:56,030
If only it were an argument.

72
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:04,440
What? He left?

73
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,080
When?

74
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:10,310
About a week ago.

75
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:14,200
Is this leading up to a divorce?

76
00:08:16,950 --> 00:08:20,040
Sorry, I shouldn't be so blunt.

77
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:25,200
When he asked to break up,
did he mean a divorce?

78
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,440
That's usually what it means, yes.

79
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,650
Thought so.

80
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:34,990
You know, I was over the moon

81
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:39,750
to hear Ouji say he actually liked me.

82
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:43,870
I know. I witnessed your elation firsthand.

83
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:46,500
Can you blame me?

84
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:50,950
I suddenly became the heroine
after living as an extra my whole life.

85
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:54,130
- Fair enough.
- I was speeding towards my happy end,

86
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:58,250
as the Ouji I dreamed of turned my way.

87
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:02,430
He chose to love me, to hug boring ol' me.

88
00:09:02,430 --> 00:09:04,520
Sounds straight out of a drama, right?

89
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,040
Sure does.

90
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:12,040
But reality looks towards what happens next.

91
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,850
You won't protest the break up?

92
00:09:15,850 --> 00:09:18,650
I already told him I wanted to stay.

93
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:22,550
Why not be more clingy about it?

94
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,740
I couldn't be.

95
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:29,030
<i>Girls would come at me aggressively
in the name of "love".</i>

96
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:32,070
<i>Eventually, I got fed up with it all.</i>

97
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:36,610
Because I wasn't any better.

98
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:41,260
I was just like those people
who cornered him in the first place.

99
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:45,030
I pushed my expectations onto him.

100
00:09:45,030 --> 00:09:50,140
You couldn't help it. You were a fan of his.

101
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:53,620
I know that.

102
00:09:54,950 --> 00:10:01,130
But I realize now how it was suffocating him.

103
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:04,310
You couldn't know. He never told you.

104
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:05,820
Right?

105
00:10:05,820 --> 00:10:10,440
Anyone would think Ouji
was a romance powerhouse.

106
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,030
I suppose.

107
00:10:12,030 --> 00:10:14,400
You are too, Akina.

108
00:10:15,230 --> 00:10:16,960
I guess.

109
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:21,700
But I'm a weakling when it comes to romance.

110
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:25,350
- That, you are.
- No need to affirm it.

111
00:10:25,350 --> 00:10:27,520
Anyway, I thought a weakling like me

112
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:31,360
would never get through to a guy like him.

113
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:33,880
So since he finally looked my way,

114
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:37,710
I thought he'd notice my efforts,
and make the first move.

115
00:10:37,710 --> 00:10:38,700
How bold.

116
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:43,840
But I guess I was pressuring him after all.

117
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:49,580
I never once gave Ouji's feelings a thought.

118
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:54,910
He looked like he was really struggling...

119
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:17,480
Haru.

120
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:20,880
To tell you the truth...

121
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,210
No, never mind.

122
00:11:30,210 --> 00:11:32,000
Say...

123
00:11:33,010 --> 00:11:38,840
What does it mean to be a weakling
or powerhouse...

124
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,980
when it comes to romance?

125
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:43,350
Huh?

126
00:11:43,350 --> 00:11:46,020
Is the one who fell first the weakling?

127
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:48,780
Is there no equality when it comes to love?

128
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:53,620
I guess so.

129
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:57,600
Then that makes me a fellow weakling.

130
00:11:58,180 --> 00:11:59,600
Huh?

131
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,810
What?

132
00:12:02,380 --> 00:12:05,080
You've fallen for someone?

133
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,800
What? Akina, in love?

134
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:12,320
Akina, who prefers sex over romance, in love?

135
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:16,050
You could say one thing led to the other...

136
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:20,460
A brothel?

137
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:21,950
A brothel, like, a brothel?

138
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:26,340
Don't make me repeat myself.
I'm just as surprised.

139
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:29,780
You look so cute right now, Akina.

140
00:12:29,780 --> 00:12:35,900
So you fell for this "therapist"?

141
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:41,940
I know. I know you want to call me stupid.

142
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:47,310
No, well... Do you love him for his body?

143
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,160
You don't?

144
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,950
I don't know.

145
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:58,160
Of course, he's always making me feel good.

146
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:00,040
But I go and check his reviews,

147
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:04,010
and feel weird knowing he does this
with other women.

148
00:13:04,010 --> 00:13:07,020
I get sad, and miss him when he leaves, too.

149
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:08,640
So do I love him physically?

150
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,780
I think it's more than that.

151
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:12,930
Right? I thought so.

152
00:13:18,010 --> 00:13:22,920
Powerhouses can become weaklings too, okay?

153
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:27,640
Relationships that aren't equal,
are pointless.

154
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:35,110
So I'm seeing him again later tonight.

155
00:13:35,110 --> 00:13:36,930
What happened to it being pointless?

156
00:13:36,930 --> 00:13:38,480
They're two separate matters.

157
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:41,430
If I have the money to see him, I'll pay.

158
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:47,110
Akina, you're you, powerhouse or not.

159
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:48,790
What's that supposed to mean?

160
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:51,150
I mean, you're super cool.

161
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:01,940
Dear.

162
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:04,380
Dear.

163
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:08,420
What's wrong? You're spacing out.

164
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:10,160
Sorry.

165
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:13,520
The sink. You're leaving it running.

166
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:18,490
Aren't you always talking about conservation?

167
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:20,990
Sorry.

168
00:14:23,140 --> 00:14:25,800
Are you out the entire day tomorrow?

169
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,400
Yeah.

170
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:31,300
I'll be doing makeup
for a stage play poster shoot.

171
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:34,020
You're still doing makeup work?

172
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:36,640
I thought you were going to look
for better gigs.

173
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,260
Hello?

174
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:53,550
Sorry, I know we promised not to call...

175
00:14:53,550 --> 00:14:56,130
It's okay. So?

176
00:14:56,130 --> 00:14:58,400
<i>It wasn't about us.</i>

177
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:03,170
The article.

178
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:05,070
Do you know Ryuhei Sato?

179
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:07,520
He's often cast as a main lead.

180
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,180
No, I don't think so.

181
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,580
I don't know who his partner was, but...

182
00:15:17,780 --> 00:15:19,440
Fuyumi?

183
00:15:21,150 --> 00:15:23,580
I hear you.

184
00:15:24,370 --> 00:15:26,300
Thank goodness.

185
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,820
<i>Fuyumi.</i>

186
00:15:27,820 --> 00:15:30,210
Can we meet sometime soon?

187
00:15:30,210 --> 00:15:32,150
I want to speak to you, in person.

188
00:15:34,740 --> 00:15:37,000
I can't think about that now.

189
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,330
<i>Sorry, I'll text you back.</i>

190
00:15:57,390 --> 00:16:00,630
My stomach was hurting.

191
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:02,230
I see.

192
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:05,380
Were you speaking to someone?

193
00:16:06,210 --> 00:16:09,460
I thought I heard some voices.

194
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:12,670
I was watching a video.

195
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:16,840
Watch it only after you finish cleaning up.

196
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:19,840
Sorry.

197
00:17:11,070 --> 00:17:12,870
[Naoki]

198
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:24,950
Let me go.

199
00:17:24,950 --> 00:17:26,730
Why do you keep ignoring my texts?

200
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:28,870
What are you talking about?

201
00:17:28,870 --> 00:17:31,550
You're the one who called me easy,

202
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:33,110
and told me to buy a man.

203
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:37,050
- I was only...
- Well, thanks for the great advice.

204
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:38,830
- Huh?
- Bye.

205
00:17:38,830 --> 00:17:40,830
Wait.

206
00:17:40,830 --> 00:17:42,960
Don't tell me you actually bought a man.

207
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:45,240
Like I said, you told me to.

208
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,340
Then it can be me, right?

209
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:49,920
Hey, let go!

210
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:53,450
Hey!

211
00:17:53,450 --> 00:17:56,620
If you're doing it with a dude
who sells himself, do it with me instead.

212
00:17:56,620 --> 00:17:58,490
Screw off! Let me go!

213
00:17:58,490 --> 00:18:00,250
Why're you acting like a virgin?

214
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:02,780
- You're used to this, right?
- Stop!

215
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:04,840
Stop it!

216
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:26,570
Akina, are you alright?

217
00:18:26,570 --> 00:18:28,280
Naoki...

218
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:34,380
The hell? Piss off, man!

219
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:40,010
Well, I mean... This was a play.

220
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:41,610
She wanted to do it outside.

221
00:18:41,610 --> 00:18:43,060
Like hell I did.

222
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:45,470
Says the one buying men for herself.

223
00:18:46,310 --> 00:18:48,780
What's so wrong about that?

224
00:18:48,780 --> 00:18:51,230
I won't have sex with men I don't want to.

225
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,440
I'll pay money to have sex
with the ones I do.

226
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,540
What's so wrong about that?

227
00:18:55,540 --> 00:18:58,780
What's so wrong with living true to myself?

228
00:19:00,710 --> 00:19:04,100
Akina. Let's report him to the police.

229
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,000
H-Haru?

230
00:19:12,990 --> 00:19:14,580
Haru!

231
00:19:14,580 --> 00:19:16,630
Are you okay?

232
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:17,910
I'm fine.

233
00:19:17,910 --> 00:19:20,580
What about you?

234
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:22,340
Are you okay?

235
00:19:22,340 --> 00:19:25,900
- I'm totally fine.
- No, you're not.

236
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:27,810
What a scumbag...

237
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:34,150
Here, your phone.

238
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:36,410
Thank you.

239
00:19:36,410 --> 00:19:38,980
Sorry to get you involved in that.

240
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:46,240
Well...

241
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,560
Thank you for earlier.

242
00:19:49,210 --> 00:19:54,590
Haru answered your phone
when I called to ask why you were late.

243
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:57,350
She told me you may still be in the area.

244
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:59,560
I see.

245
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:02,690
I was right to come and get you.

246
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:07,070
Then I'll get going.

247
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:08,540
Please take care of Akina for me.

248
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:11,860
- Of course.
- Thank you.

249
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:56,010
Do you do that huffing around Haru, too?

250
00:20:56,010 --> 00:20:57,550
What huffing?

251
00:20:57,550 --> 00:21:04,530
It's that narcissistic pity smirk
you do sometimes.

252
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:08,460
You're only satisfying yourself doing that.

253
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,950
Why?

254
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:27,130
I thought I'd made a pathetic excuse.

255
00:21:34,190 --> 00:21:35,910
What happened?

256
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:38,870
I tripped.

257
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,400
What are you doing?

258
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:57,410
Where'd I put the first aid kit...

259
00:22:00,020 --> 00:22:03,400
You, why do you trip so much?

260
00:22:04,030 --> 00:22:06,420
Whoops, slipped back into it again.

261
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:12,220
<i>What's so wrong with living true to myself?</i>

262
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,570
Ouji.

263
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:20,050
I can't help it, habits are hard to break.

264
00:22:20,050 --> 00:22:21,810
Ouji.

265
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:30,580
I want to stay with you.

266
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:35,660
I want us to stay together.

267
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,300
But that's...

268
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:44,280
I've loved you all this time,
and you finally looked my way,

269
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:47,880
so why do we have to break up now?

270
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:50,300
You can't expect anything from me, you know?

271
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:53,760
